__Edit:__ The [History page](https://til.micro.blog/history/) now includes the latest updates; covering June, July, and the first week in August.

In those weeks we saw;

- the public release of Bookshelves;
- details of Micro Camp;
- more open-sourced native apps;
- the return of Micro Monday;
- and a new member of the team!

__TIP:__ If you want to contribute to the platform you can use two public spaces;

* [Indie Microblogging](https://microblogging.slack.com/), the official Slack with multiple channels for various types of ideas and discussion.
* [Micro.blog GitHub](https://github.com/microdotblog), the repositories for code and content-based contributions.
